    <summary>Chocolatey is your machine level NuGet repository. Think executables/application packages, not library packages.</summary>
    <description>Think executables/application packages, not library packages.  This is what the Chocolatey NuGet goodness is for.
Chocolatey allows you to install application nuggets and run executables from anywhere.  
If you have an executable in the tools folder of your package named bob.exe. Then you can type

chocolatey install yourPackageName
followed by
bob
and it will run your application executable.</description>
